---
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
---
<style>
.liquid-purple-burst {
  position: absolute;
  top: 50px;
  right: -200px;
  height: 800px;
  width: 800px;
  background: radial-gradient(circle, rgba(153, 102, 255, .4), rgba(153, 102, 255, 0) 75%);
  border-radius: 50%;
}

@media (max-width: 1024px) {
  .liquid-purple-burst {
    top: unset;
    bottom: 0px;
    left: -250px;
  }
}
</style>

<div class="overflow-hidden py-10 lg:py-32 relative">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-10 lg:px-8">
    <div
      class="mt-40 lg:my-40 grid grid-cols-1 gap-x-8 gap-y-16 sm:gap-y-20 lg:mx-0 lg:max-w-none lg:grid-cols-2"
    >
      <div class="lg:pr-8 lg:pt-4">
        <div class="lg:max-w-lg">
          <h2 class="text-4xl font-semibold text-liquid-purple">
            Peer to Peer
          </h2>
          <p
            class="mt-2 text-7xl font-bold tracking-tight text-white"
          >
            Authenticated Communication
          </p>
          <p class="my-6 max-w-96 lg:max-w-none text-2xl text-gray-400">
            Liquid auth enables any supported authentication challenge to establish a connection between two peers.<br/>
            FIDO2? We got you<br/>
            Passkeys? Like there&apos;s no tomorrow<br/>
            Want to learn how we achieve this?<br/>
          </p>
          <a href={`${base}/architecture/deep-dive/`} class="px-10 py-2 text-md font-poppins leading-6 border-2 border-liquid-purple text-white">Deep Dive</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <img
        src={`${base}/auth_illustration.png`}
        alt="Product screenshot"
        class="w-[48rem] place-self-end -translate-y-40 max-w-none sm:w-[40rem] md:-ml-4 lg:-ml-0"
        width="2432"
        height="1442"
      />
      <div class="liquid-purple-burst"></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
